- 'Most active user' refers to the user with the highest total activity count, which is calculated by the number of log entries in the `activity_logs` table;
- 'Average activity' is the mean activity count of all users.

- 'prominent leaders' refers to users who hold the role of 'Head' in their departments;
- 'significant level of authority' refers to users with a role level greater than 2;
- 'actively contribute to the department's operations' refers to users who have recorded activity in the system.

- "left a footprint in the digital garden" refers to users who have logged activities;
- "at least one bloom to show for it" refers to users who have at least one successful activity;
- "IT department" is a specific department within the organization.

- 'Team Lead' refers to a specific role within a department;
- 'Cumulative activity count' is the sum of activity counts for all users in the same department, ordered by their first names;
- 'More than one team' means the department has at least two teams.

- "non-leaders" refers to users who are not department heads;
- "spread their influence across many branches" means they are associated with multiple departments;
- "vast organizational tree" refers to the hierarchical structure of the organization.

