- 'Court' refers to the collection of activities performed by users in that role;
- 'Crown of the most active' refers to the role with the highest total activity count.

- 'foundational activities' refer to activities with an activity type ID of 0;
- 'first half of the year' refers to the period from January 1, 2023, to May 31, 2023;
- 'like bees gathering nectar' is a metaphor for frequent and consistent participation.

- An "activity log" refers to any log entry in the `activity_logs` table that records user activities;
- "More than one activity log" implies a minimum of two activity logs;
- "Most active to least active" means the users are ordered by the number of activity logs in descending order.

- 'gatekeepers' refers to users with the role 'Admin';
- 'common folk' refers to users with the role 'User';
- 'remained active in their domain' means their status is 'Active';
- 'visited the realm more recently than the average traveler' means the last login date is later than the average last login date of all users.

- 'frequent visitors' refers to users who have logged in multiple times;
- 'digital garden' is a metaphor for the online platform or application;
- 'entered through the gate' is a metaphor for the 'Login' activity.

